  1. At k=1 (Monolith), Edge auth adds an extra network hop via
     Lambda@Edge that Cognito does not require, making Edge strictly worse.
  2. At k>1 (FaaS, Microservices), Edge saves per-function Cognito
     verification, which can offset the extra network hop.
  3. The break-even depends on the number of auth verification points (k).


